outcome_note:
-214 possible threats were identified.

-Well over half of the 214 threats were for encrypted files and all but two were located at “/Fellows/Applications & Applicants”; the remaining two encrypted files were “/Fellowship Organizations/Population Services International/psi-sl_security_kit/ANNEX15_PSI_Electronic+IMG_English_password+is-PSIaccess-.pdf” and “/Fellows/Fellows 2015-2016/Stipends/Disbursements/Bank Letters/Barber_Melissa_BankLetter.pdf.”

-Of the other identified threats, all were PUA’s, and all but two were for embedded JavaScript within pdf’s; the embedded JS pdf’s were ignored.

-The remaining two PUA’s were PUA.Html.Exploit.CVE_2015_1692-1 (found at “/Finances & Fundraising/FUNDRAISING/DonorPerfect/DonorPerfect/Using the Contact Manager in DonorPerfect Online (Contacts)_files/ScriptResource(7).axd”) and PUA.Win.Packer.WwpackV-1 (“/Photos/2011 Benefit/10.0_Iupdate.exe”);

-The following files were deleted: “/Fellowship Organizations/Population Services International/psi-sl_security_kit/ANNEX15_PSI_Electronic+IMG_English_password+is-PSIaccess-.pdf,” “/Fellows/Fellows 2015-2016/Stipends/Disbursements/Bank Letters/Barber_Melissa_BankLetter.pdf," and “/Photos/2011 Benefit/10.0_Iupdate.exe.”

-The following directories were deleted: ”/Fellows/Applications & Applicants” and ”/Finances & Fundraising/FUNDRAISING/DonorPerfect/DonorPerfect”
- 4 instances of CNN patterns found; no action taken due to format of file (.wav) and BE error producing false positives.
-40 instances of duplicate files were deleted
Disk Images successfully created for disks001-disk008
Created disk image for disk009 using the FC5025.

Virus checks on disk009 and optical001 completed.

- 2 instances of flag words found; actions logged

- No ccn or pii found.
